        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 18 at 3:26PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 326 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 7 miles southeast of Truckton to 10
miles northeast of Punkin Center, or extending from 34 miles
northeast of Pueblo Airport to 24 miles south of Limon, moving south
at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Punkin Center, Forder and Kutch.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Heavy rain is occurring with these storms and may lead to flooding.
Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
